{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a font letter spacing semantic token lineHeightLabelXLarge,","        \/\/ two semantic font line height spacing tokens will be defined in Figma and generated by tokenator because","        \/\/ its value can vary if compact or regular modes.","        \/\/ They can be declared in protocol FontSemanticTokens,","        \/\/ and defined automaticaly in OUDSTheme+FontSemanticTokens extension","        var lineHeightLabelXLargeMobile: FontLineHeightSemanticToken { FontRawTokens.lineHeight450 }","        var lineHeightLabelXLargeTablet: FontLineHeightSemanticToken { FontRawTokens.lineHeight450 }","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level line height semantic token for lineHeightLabelXLarge","        \/\/ inside FontMultipleSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+FontMultipleSemanticTokens extension","        var lineHeightLabelXLarge: MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens {","            MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens(compact: lineHeightLabelXLargeMobile, regular: lineHeightLabelXLargeTablet)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same value is used whatever the size class is","        var lineHeightLabelXLarge: MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens { MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens(lineHeightLabelXLargeMobile) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated font line height semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level color semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."]},{"style":"note","name":"Since","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"0.8.0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Tokens for semantics"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens"},"abstract":[{"text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/FontLineHeightSemanticToken","type":"reference"},{"text":" depending to size classes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens from ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" inside one object.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If a font line height token exists with its value depending to the size class, it must be packed in such ``MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens`","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontLineHeightSemanticTokens","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(cs)NSObject"],"title":"Inherits From"},{"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(pl)NSObject","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s7CVarArgP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s28Custo